The course introduces the vocabulary related to the following topics: cafe and shop; year and events; sightseeings; health and appearance; home and furniture; holidays.
Grammar: cases, verbs, numbers, consonant alternations, adpositsions, reflexive verbs, diminutives.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to continue the acquisition of Latvian, with special emphasis put on verbs and the reading/translating of formal/informal texts. Another aim is to be able to discuss both amongst each other and with the lecturer on simple topics (achieved through the listening of everyday speech (audio, video)).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the students will be able to 
1) read and understand simple texts
2) hold conversations on a limited range of topics
3) write short essays
4) have acquired a core of the basic structures of grammar
